    <p>
        
            
                 
            
        
        I am going to post much more on healing and the healing ministry. I thought I would begin with basics about the healing ministry just to get you started.<br><br><h3>Background</h3><br><br>The healing ministry began when the Charismatic Renewal began in the 1960s. A group of people prayed to receive the Holy Spirit at <a href="http://www.duq.edu/" target="_blank">Duquesne University</a> in Pennsylvania. The Holy Spirit came down and many received the gifts of the Holy Spirit. Thus was born the healing ministry.<br><br><h3>Where is the healing ministry based?</h3><br><br>The Bible of course! Jesus Himself healed many people. In fact, He told us to lay hands on the sick, and they will recover (Mark 16:18). Jesus used the laying-on-of-hands when he healed people. He healed the way that was best for the person being healed. Sometimes touch was used, sometimes a word was spoken.<br><br><h3>Why is the healing ministry important today?</h3><br><br>Many people don't realize the importance of praying over people. People will say, "We don't have to pray over people. We will just pray for them. Miracles were only in Jesus' time; they don't happen now." They will also state that we are called to suffer and not be healed. Sometimes, we are called to suffer. This doesn't mean that Jesus doesn't want us to ask for healing, however. Give me a break! Jesus Himself asked God to "let this cup pass from me." He said, "But not my will but thine be done." Jesus wants us to come to Him for healing. He always heals, but not always in the way we want him to.<br><br>Jesus calls us to be his instruments, not only the clergy! We are all baptized, so we can pray over people. We always say, "I'll pray for you." Nine times out of 10 we forget. Plus, some people, though they appreciate those words, don't feel any better. Sometimes they just need someone to pray over them. You'd be surprised at how God works.<br><br>We need healing more than ever before in this day and age. The Holy Spirit gave us the gift of healing for a reason. We need to step out in faith, and let the Lord use us as he wills.<br><div style="width:300px;margin:12px 0px 12px 12px;clear:both;float:right"><script type="text/javascript"><!--
google_ad_client = "pub-7242869414180671";
/* C2 300x250 */
google_ad_slot = "1297666708";
google_ad_width = 300;
google_ad_height = 250;
//-->
</script>
<script type="text/javascript"
src="http://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/show_ads.js">
</script></div> <br><br><h3>Who is called to pray over people?</h3><br><br>EVERYBODY! Clergy are very busy. They expect us to help them out a bit! Don't be afraid to step out in faith. Follow the Holy Spirit!<br><br><h3>Do you have to have the gift of healing to pray over people?</h3><br><br>If you had to have the gift of healing, the world would be a complete disaster. Think of how tired people who have the gift of healing would be if we didn't help them out. The answer then? No, anyone can pray over people. Obviously we all have different gifts, and some people do have the gift of healing. However, God uses everybody as He wills.<br><br><h3>Do you have to have the gift of tongues to pray over people?</h3><br><br>No way! Yes, this gift is very beneficial. However, don't worry if you don't have it. Just pray from the heart. More on tongues at a later time.<br><br><h3>How do you begin praying over people.</h3><br><br>Well, it's easy! If you have a friend who is suffering, ask them if you can pray with them. "May I pray with you?" You'd be surprised as to how many people yearn for you to ask that.<br>Start simple. Say something like, "Lord, I pray for ------, and I ask you to bring Your healing upon him/her. I pray for Your will to be done. Please bring Your healing and heal him/her from head to toe. We praise and thank You for what You have done and will do. In Jesus' Name, AMEN!"<br><br>Don't get nervous, it doesn't have to be that long. You can even just lay hands and not say anything. Do what you are comfortable doing. Follow the Holy Spirit. If you have Holy water or Holy Oil, I certainly recommend that you use that. Also, if you are praying for physical healing, I recommend laying hands on the area that needs healing (within reason). Trust me, this is very comforting for the person. Take it from someone who knows.<br><br>I hope this helps. Ask questions and please comment. Remember, no question or comment is silly or stupid!<br><br>God bless,<br>Christine
